What is Unity Build?
Unity build is the processes of building a program using just 1 file (often main.c). For reaching this in C programming language we can do this:
make the entry file (main.c), then make all the files that you need (like lib.c works.c foo.c) and then Import those files inside the main.c file.
E.f:
#include &lt;stdio.h&gt;

// unity build includes
#include &lt;foo.c&gt;
#include &lt;works.c&gt;
#include &lt;lib.c&gt;

...
this approach works, because the #include keyword will literally replace the files that we want and put it inside the entry (main) file.
then we can just compile the entry (main) to get the outputs.
